                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2002-05-09</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>A lot of these books just regurgitate specs or heavily technical info...the rest will tell you stuff you can find in any wireless hype magazine.  I think Paul Bedell puts the time in to bridge the technologies, show where corelations are, and gives you a solid understanding on where the industry has evolved from.  If you deal with wireless networks, buy it; you need it.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Good and simple start</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
