                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-12-13</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book is marvelous for the untechnical reader.  I have 23 years in the IT and it was easy to read.  To be certain, you must follow it up with more practical books (ex. Rhoton or Jimenez) for business implementation. Or even detail books (Rappaport) for technology.  Other reviewers wrote that this book omits important parts.  Every book will. You can not cover all of wireless in one book.  This book is simple for end user.</span>
                  
              
